cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with audio signal processing and localization of acoustic reflectors.
- cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing) is also likely as the paper deals with spatial audio and source separation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper proposes new algorithms for acoustic reflector localization.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper deals with audio signal processing and scene reconstruction.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possibility as the proposed ellipsoid tangent sample consensus (ETSAC) method exploits ellipsoid properties to localize the reflector, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision.
